---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const lastUpdated = 'July 3, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="BIMLine Gépész Kft.'s privacy policy: what data we process on our website, our use of cookies, Google Analytics measurement, and your rights as a data subject."
  path="/en/adatkezeles/"
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8" data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Legal Notice</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.1rem)] leading-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted">Effective: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose-bimline mt-10">
        <p>
          This notice explains, transparently and in detail, what personal data BIMLine Gépész
          Kft. (the <strong>"Data Controller"</strong>) processes while operating the
          <code>bimline.hu</code> website (the <strong>"Website"</strong>), for what purpose, on
          what legal basis, and for how long — and what rights this gives you as a data subject.
          This notice is based on Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the
          Council (the <strong>"GDPR"</strong>) and Hungarian Act CXII of 2011 on the Right of
          Informational Self-Determination and Freedom of Information.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Data controller details</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Name:</strong> BIMLine Gépész Kft.</li>
          <li><strong>Registered seat:</strong> 1053 Budapest, Ferenczy István utca 28., Hungary</li>
          <li><strong>Company registration number:</strong> 01-09-434556</li>
          <li><strong>Tax number:</strong> 26710156-2-41</li>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@bimline.hu">hello@bimline.hu</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. What data we process, and why</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Contact / quote request form</h3>
        <p>
          Through the Website's contact form, we request the following data: name, company name
          (optional), email address, phone number (optional), a project description, the design
          baselines you have available, and — if provided — links to drawings.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> responding to your inquiry, providing a quote or consultation.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal basis:</strong> your consent under GDPR Article 6(1)(a), given by ticking the checkbox when you submit the form.</li>
          <li><strong>Recipients of the data:</strong> form submissions arrive to us by email (via Google Workspace), and — if you provided an email address — you also receive an automatic confirmation.</li>
          <li><strong>Retention period:</strong> a maximum of 2 years after the inquiry is closed, or until consent is withdrawn.</li>
          <li><strong>Withdrawing consent:</strong> at any time, without justification, by emailing <a href="mailto:hello@bimline.hu">hello@bimline.hu</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Cookies and website analytics</h3>
        <p>
          The Website uses cookies. Cookies are small text files that your browser stores on your
          device while you visit. Some are essential for the Website to function; others — only
          with your consent — serve statistical purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first time you visit the Website, a cookie settings banner appears, where you can
          decide, category by category, which cookies to allow. Cookies outside the "Necessary"
          category (currently: Statistics) only activate after you accept them — before that, no
          non-essential cookie is placed on your device.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto mt-6 rounded-xl border border-line">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-surface2/60 text-left">
                <th class="p-3 font-display font-semibold">Category</th>
                <th class="p-3 font-display font-semibold">Cookie / provider</th>
                <th class="p-3 font-display font-semibold">Purpose</th>
                <th class="p-3 font-display font-semibold">Lifetime</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-muted">
              <tr class="border-t border-line/60">
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Necessary</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top"><code>bimline_cookie_consent</code> (first-party, on the Website's own domain)</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Remembers your cookie preferences, so you don't need to set them again on every visit.</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">180 days</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-line/60">
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Statistics</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top"><code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code> — Google Analytics 4 (Google Ireland Limited)</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Website analytics: where visitors come from, what content they click on, and how much time they spend on the site. Only active with consent.</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Up to 14 months (Google default)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-line/60">
                <td class="p-3 align-top">Marketing</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">No active marketing cookies at this time</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">This category is prepared for a possible future feature; enabling it currently starts no tracking. If this changes, we will update this notice.</td>
                <td class="p-3 align-top">—</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4">
          You can change your cookie settings, or withdraw previously given consent, at any time
          via the "Cookie settings" button in the footer, or with the button below:
        </p>
        <p class="not-prose">
          <button type="button" id="reopenCookiePrefsBtn" class="mt-1 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-line text-sm font-semibold hover:border-accent/60 transition">Open cookie settings</button>
        </p>

        <h2>3. Google Analytics — in more detail</h2>
        <p>
          If you consent to statistics cookies, the Website uses Google Analytics 4, operated by
          Google Ireland Limited (Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland), and data may
          also be processed by Google LLC (United States). The legal basis for the transfer to the
          US is the adequacy framework adopted by the European Commission (the EU–U.S. Data
          Privacy Framework), as well as the Standard Contractual Clauses included in Google's
          general terms of service. You can read more about Google's data processing in Google's
          privacy policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The measurement ID (property) used only starts actually sending data once you give the
          consent described above; until then, the tracking script doesn't even load in your
          browser.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data transfers</h2>
        <p>
          The Data Controller processes personal data primarily itself, and with the assistance of
          the data processors named above (Google Ireland Limited / Google LLC; and, for the
          contact form, the Google Workspace email service). Beyond this, we do not share your data
          with third parties, except where required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your rights as a data subject</h2>
        <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding the personal data we process about you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — you can ask for information about what data of yours we process.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — you can ask us to correct inaccurate data.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten") — you can ask us to delete your data if it's no longer needed, or if you withdraw your consent.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to restriction of processing.</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Right to object</strong> to processing.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — you can ask to receive the data you provided in a structured, commonly used format, or have it transmitted to another controller.</li>
          <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent at any time</strong>, which does not affect the lawfulness of processing carried out before the withdrawal.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@bimline.hu">hello@bimline.hu</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Remedies</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe that the processing of your data violates the GDPR or Hungarian data
          protection law, you can lodge a complaint with the Hungarian National Authority for Data
          Protection and Freedom of Information (NAIH):
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> 1055 Budapest, Falk Miksa utca 9-11., Hungary</li>
          <li><strong>Postal address:</strong> 1363 Budapest, Pf. 9., Hungary</li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> +36 (1) 391-1400</li>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:ugyfelszolgalat@naih.hu">ugyfelszolgalat@naih.hu</a></li>
          <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.naih.hu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.naih.hu</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You may also bring a claim before a court; such proceedings fall within the jurisdiction
          of the regional courts (törvényszék), and — at your choice — may be brought before the
          court with jurisdiction over your place of residence or habitual stay.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to this notice</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to amend this notice, particularly in the event of legal changes or
          changes to our data-processing practices on the Website. The current version is always
          available on this page, with the effective date shown at the top.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.getElementById('reopenCookiePrefsBtn')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    (window as unknown as { bimlineOpenCookiePreferences?: () => void }).bimlineOpenCookiePreferences?.();
  });
</script>
